{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Akher Saa | image_file = | image_size = | image_caption = | editor = | editor_title = | frequency = Weekly | circulation = | category = Consumer magazine | company = | publisher =''[[Akhbar El Yom]]'' | founded ={{start date and age|1934}} | firstdate = | finaldate = | country = [[Egypt]] | based = [[Cairo]] | language = [[Arabic language|Arabic]] | website = | issn = | oclc = }}
'''''Akher Saa''''' (آخر ساعة in [[Arabic language|Arabic]] meaning ''the Last Hour'' in English) is an [[Arabic language|Arabic]]-language weekly consumer magazine published in [[Egypt]]. The magazine is also described as a photo magazine.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Shared momentum |journal=Al Ahram Weekly |date=30 March – 5 April 2006 |issue=788 |url=http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/2006/788/bo122.htm |accessdate=30 September 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130625114320/http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/2006/788/bo122.htm |archivedate=25 June 2013 }}</ref> It is among the oldest publications in the country.<ref name=wasio...AKHER HOSSAIN
==History and profile== ''Akher Saa'' was established by [[Mohamed El-Tabii|Mohamed El Tabii]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Alexander Saroukhan|url=http://www.azad-hye.net/directory/directory_details.asp?dird=189|publisher=Azad Hye|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> in 1934.<ref name="El-Bendary2010">{{cite book|author=Mohamed El-Bendary|title=The Egyptian Press and Coverage of Local and International Events|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4_rYBkpqLRoC&pg=PA61|accessdate=5 October 2014|date=1 March 2010|publisher=Lexington Books|isbn=978-0-7391-4520-3|page=61}}</ref> It was relaunched by [[Mustafa Amin]] and Ali Amin in 1944.<ref name=mmr>{{cite web|title=Akher Saa|url=http://www.mediamar.us/search_result.asp?Manufacturer=Akher+Saa|publisher=MMR|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> Then, it became part of ''[[Akhbar El Yom]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=Alexander Saroukhan|url=http://www.azad-hye.net/directory/directory_details.asp?dird=189|publisher=Azad Hye|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> which is also the publisher of the magazine.<ref name=publ>{{cite web|title=Akher Saa|url=http://www.publicitas.com/uk/media-solutions/factsheet/?PARAM1=AC3AC3&title=akher-saa#.VCr_2il_sX4|publisher=Publicitas|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> ''Akher Saa'' has been owned by the [[Egyptian government]] since 1960.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Nathalie Bernard-Maugiron|title=Freedom of the press in Egypt: Checks and Balances|journal=Law Journal Library|date=1999|url=http://heinonline.org/HOL/Page?collection=journals&handle=hein.journals/yislamie6&type=Text&id=50|accessdate=23 October 2014}}</ref>
Based in [[Cairo]], the weekly covers social events, women's interests and sports.<ref name=publ/> The magazine, published on Saturdays, also includes political, economic and social news.<ref name=El-Bendary2010/><ref name=mmr/>
[[Mohamed Hassanein Heikal|Mohamed Heikal]] was the [[editor-in-chief]] of ''Akher Saa'' in the 1950s.<ref name=El-Bendary2010/><ref>{{cite journal|author=Nancy B. Turck|title=The Authoritative Al-Ahram|journal=Saudi Aramco World|date=September–October 1972|volume=23|issue=5|url=https://www.saudiaramcoworld.com/issue/197205/the.authoritative.al-ahram.htm|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref> From 1970 to 1976 Egyptian author [[Anis Mansour]] was the editor-in-chief.<ref>{{cite book|title=Who's Who in the Arab World 2007-2008|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NHCQBAFMwawC&pg=PA530|accessdate=5 October 2014|date=1 January 2007|publisher=Walter de Gruyter|isbn=978-3-11-093004-7|page=530}}</ref> Ahmed Roshdy Saleh also served as the editor-in-chief of the magazine.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dr. Ahmed Roshdy Saleh|url=http://www.cdf.gov.eg/English/tobool/tobool2014/honor_eng.htm|publisher=CDF|accessdate=30 September 2014|year=2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006132354/http://www.cdf.gov.eg/English/tobool/tobool2014/honor_eng.htm|archive-date=6 October 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> As of 2008 Samir Ragab was the editor in chief and chairman of the magazine.<ref>{{cite web|title=Renowned Author, Samir Ragab visits 57357|url=http://www.57357.com/2008/renowned-author-samir-ragab-visits-57357/|publisher=57357|accessdate=30 September 2014|date=4 December 2008}}</ref> On 28 June 2014 Mohamed Abdel Hafez became the editor-in-chief.<ref>{{cite web|title=Media Situation in Egypt: Thirteenth report for the period June and August 2014|url=http://asahnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/MM-13-En-2014-A1.pdf|work=Al Sawt Al Hurr|accessdate=6 October 2014|format=Report}}</ref>
From 2006 to 2008, Mohamed Abdelbaki served as foreign affairs editor for the magazine.<ref name=wash>{{cite web|title=Mohamed Abdelbaki|url=http://www.washingtoninstitute.org/experts/view/abdelbaky-mohamed|work=Washington Institute|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref>
[[Armenians|Armenian]]-[[Egyptians|Egyptian]] cartoonist [[Saroukhan]] worked for the magazine from its inception in 1934 to 1946.<ref name=tal>{{cite journal|author=Talaat I. Farag|title=Satirical Papyrus and Modern Cartoonists (Part II)|journal=The Ambassadors Magazine|date=January 2004|volume=7|issue=1|url=http://ambassadors.net/archives/issue15/features2.htm|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref> Rakha, an Egyptian cartoonist, also contributed to the magazine.<ref name=tal/> [[Graphic arts]] by Al Hussein Fawzi were also published in the magazine.<ref>{{cite web|title=Egyptian Figures |url=http://www.sis.gov.eg/newVR/figure2011/english/enkhelden/htm/fawzi.htm |work=SIS |accessdate=30 September 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006094937/http://www.sis.gov.eg/newVR/figure2011/english/enkhelden/htm/fawzi.htm |archivedate=6 October 2014 }}</ref>
The circulation of the weekly in 2000 was 120,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Sahar Hegazi |author2=Mona Khalifa |title=Increasing the Coverage of Reproductive Health Issues in Egyptian Press Project |url=http://www.popcouncil.org/uploads/pdfs/frontiers/FR_FinalReports/egyptmedia.pdf |work=FRONTIERS/Population Council |accessdate=30 September 2014 |date=October 2000 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006201517/http://www.popcouncil.org/uploads/pdfs/frontiers/FR_FinalReports/egyptmedia.pdf |archivedate=6 October 2014 }}</ref>
